{"TopicId":153241,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Vortex - Light SSTO","CreatedByName":"Cupcake...","CreatedById":62843,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T10:21:43Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Cupcake...","CreatedById":62843,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T10:21:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIMPORTANT: LANDING GEAR/DROP TANK FIX FOUND PLEASE ENSURE YOU HAVE THE LATEST VERSION.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECRAFT FILE:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://goo.gl/bXzxYI\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://goo.gl/bXzxYI\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EUPDATES:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E20/12/16\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003E- Drop tanks removed due to bug. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E model added to archive.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E26/12/16 - Drop Tank/Landing Gear Fix Applied.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E11/1/17 - Visual Update.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ERECOMMENDED MOD:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/90252-121-pilot-assistant-atmospheric-piloting-aids-1131-oct-23/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/lOheqnfz3js?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPresenting the Vortex, an extremely compact light weight \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E that proves you don\u0027t have to go big to go far. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mdG4H1C.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mdG4H1C.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing its drop-tanks the craft puts out a very respectable 2.5k at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E which is enough for Munar missions or even interplanetary trips!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022yoaLjOC.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/yoaLjOC.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven without the droptanks the Vortex can still fly to Minmus and return to Kerbin as a pure \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022U6Hyo9u.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/U6Hyo9u.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe top docking port is planted smack bang on the center of mass allowing the craft to be refueled, transported or even salvaged with ease.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022DdCm5vc.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/DdCm5vc.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike the Storm and Squall that preceded it the Vortex features smooth, agile handling and is very easy to pilot. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kGPupqC.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/kGPupqC.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt borrows the light weight thermal protection from the Catalyst which is fortunate as this plane can go very, very fast indeed!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022g0WGBMY.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/g0WGBMY.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn addition to the standard single seat version there\u0027s also a duel seat edition allowing your Kerbals to take a friend into deep space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022d6DM9kh.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/d6DM9kh.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECONTROLS:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1 - Toggle Engine\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2 - Switch Engine Modes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n0 - Toggle Cockpit Doors/Speed Brake\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nABORT - Undock Top Docking Port\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPILOT NOTES:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA Joystick is highly recommended for this design and KSP in general.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce safely out the atmosphere or parked up ensure the cockpit doors are left open so the solar panels aren\u0027t deprived of sunlight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Rapier engine doesn\u0027t have an alternator so try and conserve electricity where possible and only use the landing lights when needed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe design features a very streamlined, low drag profile which can make slowing down in the atmosphere a problem! Start by deploying the landing gear as you reenter and use this to help slow the craft to subsonic speeds after which the cockpit doors can be opened to further slow the aircraft. Just ensure you close the cockpit doors before landing!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs you approach the runway it\u0027s good practice to limit the engine output to 30%.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStudies have shown the craft is 46.7% cooler with the drop-tanks detached but this is entirely optional.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecommended cruising altitude for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E model is 25,000m with speed limited to 1728m/s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESTANDARD ASCENT:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis aircraft really is a doddle to get to orbit, follow these instructions for perfect results every time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStage once to pre-heat the engine, board your Kerbal, activate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and close the cockpit doors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce the thrust maxes out stage again to release the launch clamps.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce you leave the runway fold the gear in and immediately pitch up to 5* above the horizon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf using Pilot Assist (recommended) set the craft\u0027s heading to 90*.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLeaving your hands off the stick let the craft build speed and pitch itself up to 10* above the horizon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeep the nose pointed just below the 10* line by periodically tapping the F key.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce your apoapsis reaches around 81k press 1 to kill the engine and set the craft to point prograde.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce safely out the atmosphere open the cockpit doors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis profile will leave you approx 50 units of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E for landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDROP TANK FREE ASCENT:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFollow the same steps as the standard ascent only ensure you pitch up to 10* straight away once leaving the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis profile will leave you approx 20 units of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E for landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnjoy! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCupcake...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KQZlaVV.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/KQZlaVV.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-11T08:21:27Z\u0022 title=\u002201/11/2017 08:21  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Cupcake...\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"chadgaskerman","CreatedById":155837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T16:11:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWOOOOO,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew cupcake stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI always enjoy the next instalment of a cupcake craft\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou keep amazing me with your work\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n~Chad \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hast5250","CreatedById":171653,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T17:18:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYEAH! Awsome! imma download some crafts and fly em\u0027!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Speed_Kerman","CreatedById":159538,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T23:22:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere are you hiding the oxidizer on there? I sense some trademark \u0022Cupcake Clip-Fu\u0022 here...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cupcake...","CreatedById":62843,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T23:59:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222881674\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153241\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481325747\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159538\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Speed_Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, Speed_Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere are you hiding the oxidizer on there? I sense some trademark \u0022Cupcake Clip-Fu\u0022 here...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt didn\u0027t look very nice with all those Round 8 tanks so I slid the NCS adapters over them, hope this doesn\u0027t upset the purists among you too much. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KyC3aRa.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/KyC3aRa.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn other news the duel seat D model is ready for your downloading pleasure, there\u0027s a slight drop in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EDV\u003C/abbr\u003E (around 50m/s) but nothing too major. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022c6By0Vy.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/c6By0Vy.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave fun out there! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCupcake...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cupcake...","CreatedById":62843,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-20T08:37:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeh all,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 I\u0027ve added a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E only version of the Vortex to the archive. This craft is designed to fly very fast, very high and will let two Kerbals cruise at speeds in excess of Mach 5 with enough fuel to circumnavigate Kerbin. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022jXIYcfX.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/jXIYcfX.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor cruising I\u0027d recommend using Pilot Assist to hold the plane at an altitude of 27,990. You\u0027ll also want to restrict the speed to 1620m/s otherwise you\u0027ll be flying so fast the engine will start cutting out!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00225MP0VVX.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/5MP0VVX.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs I mentioned on the main page I\u0027ve had to remove the drop-tanks on the Vortex for now due to a bug. As soon as I can diagnose the issue I\u0027ll let you all know but in the meantime this is a good opportunity to practice those Mimmus runs. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCupcake...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cupcake...","CreatedById":62843,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-25T02:19:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappy x-mas all. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/lOheqnfz3js?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnjoy!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCupcake...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-26T00:31:28Z\u0022 title=\u002212/26/2016 12:31  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Cupcake...\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ottothesilent","CreatedById":146852,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-25T14:03:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally nice build, and happy holidays to you, sir!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cupcake...","CreatedById":62843,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-26T00:09:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222900436\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153241\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482674630\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146852\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ottothesilent\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, ottothesilent said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally nice build, and happy holidays to you, sir!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd to you kind cosmonaut. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn other good news I\u0027ve finally found a fix for the landing gear/drop tank bugs that were plaguing the Vortex, \u003Cstrong\u003Eto anyone that downloaded the original files please ensure you grab the latest versions!\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022d6DM9kh.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/d6DM9kh.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnjoy! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCupcake...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-26T01:36:56Z\u0022 title=\u002212/26/2016 01:36  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Cupcake...\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Redshift OTF","CreatedById":78679,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-26T12:20:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, what\u0027s the blob on the end of the nose cone for? Is it an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters? Does it help with heat or drag?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cupcake...","CreatedById":62843,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-26T20:34:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222901029\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153241\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482754850\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278679\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Redshift OTF\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Redshift OTF said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, what\u0027s the blob on the end of the nose cone for? Is it an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters? Does it help with heat or drag?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt helps with heat, it\u0027s got a tolerance of 2600k which is more then most of the aero parts. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCupcake...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Redshift OTF","CreatedById":78679,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-27T10:10:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh I see. Interesting little trick that! I might have to use it myself. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E If it is offset into the nose cone does it have the same effect or does the game take into account the position of the thruster rather than what it is attached to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cupcake...","CreatedById":62843,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-27T10:40:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222901864\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153241\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482833412\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278679\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Redshift OTF\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Redshift OTF said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh I see. Interesting little trick that! I might have to use it myself. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E If it is offset into the nose cone does it have the same effect or does the game take into account the position of the thruster rather than what it is attached to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt doesn\u0027t matter what it\u0027s attached to as long as it\u0027s at the front of the craft. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCupcake...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}